## 2. Phase-by-Phase Execution Tasks

### PHASE 1: Core Infrastructure ([base_stage.py](file:///c:/Users/Tufan/Desktop/yolo8_proje_goruntu/stages/base_stage.py) Enhancement)

#### Task 1.1: Logitech Camera Wrapper
Create a `LogitechCamera` class in [camera/](file:///c:/Users/Tufan/Desktop/yolo8_proje_goruntu/camera/) similar to [ZedCamera](file:///c:/Users/Tufan/Desktop/yolo8_proje_goruntu/camera/zed_camera.py#38-247):
- [open()](file:///c:/Users/Tufan/Desktop/yolo8_proje_goruntu/camera/zed_camera.py#83-124), [close()](file:///c:/Users/Tufan/Desktop/yolo8_proje_goruntu/camera/zed_camera.py#125-131), [grab_frame()](file:///c:/Users/Tufan/Desktop/yolo8_proje_goruntu/camera/zed_camera.py#138-165), [is_open](file:///c:/Users/Tufan/Desktop/yolo8_proje_goruntu/camera/zed_camera.py#132-135) property
- Uses `cv2.CAP_DSHOW` backend, `CAP_PROP_BUFFERSIZE=1`
- Thread-safe (will be read from worker threads)

#### Task 1.2: 1D LiDAR Serial Parser — Benewake TF03
Create `hardware/lidar_interface.py`:
- **Model:** Benewake TF03
- **Serial config:** 115200 baud, 8-N-1 (configurable 9600–921600)
- **Protocol:** Binary, 9-byte fixed packet:
  ```
  Byte 0: 0x59 (frame header)
  Byte 1: 0x59 (frame header)
  Byte 2: Dist_L (distance low byte, cm)
  Byte 3: Dist_H (distance high byte, cm)
  Byte 4: Strength_L (signal strength low)
  Byte 5: Strength_H (signal strength high)
  Byte 6: Temp_L (sensor temperature low)
  Byte 7: Temp_H (sensor temperature high)
  Byte 8: Checksum (sum of bytes 0-7, low 8 bits)
  ```
- **Distance formula:** `distance_cm = Dist_H * 256 + Dist_L`
- Non-blocking `poll_distance() → float | None` method (returns meters)
- Continuous background polling thread with latest-value buffer
- Checksum validation, timeout/error handling for serial dropouts
- Signal strength threshold for unreliable readings

> [!NOTE]
> LiDAR serial port: **COM3** (115200 baud). [system_config.py](file:///c:/Users/Tufan/Desktop/yolo8_proje_goruntu/config/system_config.py)'de yapılandırılacak.

#### Task 1.3: Parallax Shift Function
Add to [base_stage.py](file:///c:/Users/Tufan/Desktop/yolo8_proje_goruntu/stages/base_stage.py):
```python
def calculate_parallax_shift(self, depth_m: float, offset_x_mm: float, offset_y_mm: float) -> tuple[float, float]:
    """Returns (shift_x_px, shift_y_px) for targeting correction."""
```
Offset values will be read from [system_config.py](file:///c:/Users/Tufan/Desktop/yolo8_proje_goruntu/config/system_config.py) (configured after physical measurement).

#### Task 1.4: Dual-Engine Model Manager
Create a helper that manages TensorRT engine loading:
- Load batch=1 engine for single-camera stages
- Load batch=2 engine when both cameras feed YOLO
- Handle engine switching during Spotter→Tracker handover

